n=\r\nt&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;brands&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;/font&gt;. Though cacao beans are drying to the body and not great for a vata=\r\n person like me, they are better than coffee and tea. So I take it occasion=\r\nally for the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;fl=\r\navinoids in them&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb=\r\n(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; backgr=\r\nound-color: transparent; font-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; fon=\r\nt-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; background-color: transparent;\n font-=\r\nstyle: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Balance is the key. Eat what is good=\r\n for you 80% of the time. Eat other things now and then, but balance them w=\r\nith ingredients that compensate for their bad qualities. Then your body wil=\r\nl get balanced nutrition. Some familiarity with ayurveda is very very usefu=\r\nl (read &quot;Prakriti: Your Ayurvedic Constitution&quot; and &quot;Yoga of Herbs&quot;). The n=\r\notions on nutrition and health in popular culture are utterly nonsensical.&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12px; =\r\nfont-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; background-color: transparent; fon=\r\nt-style: normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=3D&quot;=\r\n2&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13px;font-fa=\r\nmily:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-=\r\nstyle: