so that they burn fully.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color=\r\n:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica,\n sans-serif=\r\n;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, hel=\r\nvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;S=\r\necondly, things offered should have enough air circulation. Even if I offer=\r\n small items, things stuck in the middle of a big pile do not get enough ox=\r\nygen to burn. Offering materials at a reasonable pace and spreading them th=\r\nroughout the firepit, may help.&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sa=\r\nns-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/spa=\r\nn&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:ar=\r\nial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;span&gt;Even firewood logs will burn better and brighter if they have air ci=\r\nrculation. If a wood log touches fire pit bottom/walls only at its\n two edg=\r\nes and is suspended in air\n elsewhere, it will burn better because of air s=\r\nupply. Otherwise, edges of the portion without air circulation may keep rel=\r\neasing smoke.&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, =\r\n0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-=\r\ncolor:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sa=\r\nns-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;As things b=\r\nurn, if you turn them around or mix them up so that everything burns well (=\r\ntongs may be used), it can help you burn everything well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div =\r\nstyle=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetic=\r\na, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;=\r\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span&gt;When I offer poornahuti (a whole dry coconut) in my homa=\r\nm, I pre-arrange burnt wood coals in a structure that has nice air flow. Wh=\r\nen coconut is placed\n atop those coals, it does not crush everything (in wh=\r\nich case, some stuff under coconut or bottom of coconut may burn fully by t=\r\nhe time fire goes off), but gets suspended on the coals with most of the co=\r\nconut getting air circulation. It burns nicely from all sides, including th=\r\ne bottom. If this is not possible, you may want to turn the poornahuti arou=\r\nnd in the middle (while there is still fire) and perhaps change its positio=\r\nn/place (and offer a little more ghee then). In my case, I go into one-hour=\r\n japam after poornahuti and do not want to stop meditation in the middle to=\r\n take care of poornahuti. So I arrange things nicely beforehand. The way it=\r\n is placed, it just burns completely and everything offered before also bur=\r\nns completely, by the time fire goes off by itself.&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;It is a matter of understanding the dynami=\r\ncs of how fire and oxygen interact to burn materials and when smoke comes. =\r\nOne should try to\n learn from experience and\n draw common sense lessons.&lt;br=\r\n clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.333=\r\n3px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;f=\r\nont-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0=\r\n);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-c=\r\nolor:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Regarding shreema.org recommenda=\r\ntion (&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We extinguish the fire during the Purnahuti. Pour milk =\r\nover the burning coals&quot;, &quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Milk stands for the ocean of conscio=\r\nusness =E2=80=93 pure, white, the absence of\n all colors, attitudes. After =\r\nthe fire has purified all impurities, it \nis extinguished with pure conscio=\r\nusness.&quot;):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px=\r\n;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font=\r\n-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);f=\r\nont-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-colo=\r\nr:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Such a practice may exist in some t=\r\nraditions. In my humble, but firm, opinion, this practice is based on ignor=\r\nance and worth ignoring. When discussing this specific recommendation and t=\r\nhe quotes above, Dr Svoboda wrote to me, &quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;I definitely d=\r\no not endorse quenching homa at its end. Neither did Vimalananda&lt;/span&gt;&quot;.&lt;/=\r\nspan&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family=\r\n:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:norma=\r\nl;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.=\r\n3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica,\n sans-serif;background-color:transpare=\r\nnt;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;I believe Shree Ma and Swamiji have their hear=\r\nts in the right place and doing good dharmik work. I do admire their work a=\r\nnd wish them well. But this advice of theirs is simply nonsensical. First o=\r\nf all, milk is not a symbol of pure consciousness. Milk has a specific tast=\r\ne and color (sweetness and white) and not really a symbol of guna-less pure=\r\n consciousness. Secondly, fire is the symbol of Divinity and you should let=\r\n it process your offerings completely and give the results in due time. You=\r\n can&#39;t try to force things. Pouring milk under the pretext that it is &quot;pure=\r\n consciousness&quot; is akin to doing some sadhana and pretending that you are n=\r\now in samadhi. That only results in delusions and theatrics and not real sa=\r\nmadhi. If you want real samadhi, you need true surrender. True surrender re=\r\nquires infinite patience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0,\n 0);fon=\r\nt-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:=\r\ntransparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;colo=\r\nr:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif=\r\n;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Never ever extingui=\r\nsh homam fire. If there are practical limitations on when fire should go of=\r\nf (e.g. you need to leave), maintain a small enough fire and offer poornahu=\r\nti early enough, so that fire goes off by itself by the needed time. But yo=\r\nu can&#39;t forcefully extinguish it when fire is still burning.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;d=\r\niv style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helve=\r\ntica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-f=\r\namily:arial, helvetica,\n sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style=\r\n:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=\r\nsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span=\r\n&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;font-family:ari=\r\nal, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;=\r\n&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font=\r\n-size:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:t=\r\nransparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Someone I know does homam outside and =\r\nleaves for work. Though fire goes off before he leaves, there will be red c=\r\noals for a much longer time. Wind can make small coals fly off and so, for =\r\nsafety, he covers the homa kundam with a tightly wrapped aluminum foil. Tha=\r\nt also is like extinguishing fire because you are turning off oxygen supply=\r\n that can help fire (resident in red coals) to burn things further and cons=\r\nume them. If you make\n 2 small holes in the foil cover to\n keep oxygen flow=\r\ning, with holes being small enough that solid things cannot fly off through=\r\n them, it is safe and, at the same time, allows Agni to consume as much as =\r\nhe wants! Once you invite Agni, offer only as much as you want Him to consu=\r\nme, but do let Him consume all of it. Don&#39;t stop him forcefully in the midd=\r\nle.&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-si=\r\nze:13.3333px;font-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:tran=\r\nsparent;font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;span&gt;&lt;&lt;Also I am keen in knowing , does attending havan also burn ka=\r\nrmas ...I mean not giving any aahuti but just attending havan&gt;&gt;&lt;br cl=\r\near=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;As per &quot;Parasara Madhaveeyam&quot; (commentary o=\r\nn Parasara Smriti - authority for this age - by celebrated\n Madhavacharya, =\r\nbrother of Sayanacharya who wrote the\n celebrated commentaries on Veda), a =\r\nritual performed by oneself is 1,000,000 times more powerful than a ritual =\r\nperformed in one&#39;s name by a priest. Then sitting near a ritual performed b=\r\ny someone else is far less effective than doing a ritual by oneself. Having=\r\n said that, it may still be far more effective than most other activities w=\r\ne engage in!!!&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;The bottomline, h=\r\nowever, is the internal purity and concentration. If one is pure enough and=\r\n concentrates well, one can offer things to any external fire or even &lt;/spa=\r\nn&gt;&lt;span&gt;internal fire. If all one can do is to sit at someone else&#39;s homam =\r\nor pooja, one should go ahead and do it. If all one can do is to meditate w=\r\nhere one is, one should go ahead and do it. But, if one has a chance to do =\r\na homam, one may consider doing it.&lt;br clear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br clear=3D&quot;no=\r\nne&quot;&gt;If you don&#39;t have a group to chant mantras with but want to, chant alon=\r\ne but imagine that there are other\n people around you who are chanting. Who=\r\n knows, oneday\n you may really be surrounded by many chanting people..&lt;br c=\r\nlear=3D&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:rgb(0, 0, 0);font-size:13.3333px;f=\r\nont-family:arial, helvetica, sans-serif;background-color:transparent;font-s=\r\ntyle:normal;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Best regards,&lt;br clear=\r\n